<section class="section">
  <div class="container faq-stage">
    <div class="faq-header">
      <h2 class="section-title section-title-glow">Career coaching — frequently asked questions</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle">Answers for professionals evaluating whether career coaching is right for their situation.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-grid">
      <details class="faq-card" open>
        <summary>How much does career coaching cost at Askia?</summary>
        <p>Askia offers both targeted services (resume revision, LinkedIn, interview prep as standalone) and full coaching packages. Cost depends on scope and engagement length. Book a free strategy call and we will walk through the options that make sense for your situation — no pressure, no commitment required.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-card">
        <summary>Is career coaching worth it?</summary>
        <p>For professionals targeting roles above $100K, the ROI is almost always clear. Our clients average a $47K salary increase when we work on offer strategy, and 89% land offers within 60 days when executing the plan. Most clients recoup the investment in the first paycheck at the new role.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-card">
        <summary>How long does career coaching take?</summary>
        <p>Resume and LinkedIn revision typically takes 5–7 business days. Most clients start seeing interview traction within 21 days of completing their positioning work. Full job searches, when executed consistently, typically close within 60 days. The fastest engagements we see are people who already have strong applications but are losing at the interview stage — those usually close in 30 days.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-card">
        <summary>What is the difference between a career coach and a career counselor?</summary>
        <p>A career counselor typically helps you explore options, assess fit, and work through broader life-career alignment. A career coach — especially one like Askia — focuses on execution: how do you get from where you are now to a specific, better role. We work on the tactics of job searching: your resume, LinkedIn, interview performance, and offer negotiation. Less exploration, more momentum.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-card">
        <summary>Do you work with people who are currently employed?</summary>
        <p>Yes — most of our clients are employed and doing a confidential search. We help you run a focused, targeted search without disrupting your current role, and we structure the coaching around your availability.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-card">
        <summary>What industries does Askia specialize in?</summary>
        <p>Askia specializes in tech (software engineering, data, product, DevOps, AI/ML, cybersecurity, engineering management), business (operations, strategy, supply chain, project management), finance (FP&A, corporate finance, accounting, controller), sales and marketing, people and HR, healthcare administration, and legal/compliance.</p>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

